    <div id="ai-page" class="content1" class="p">
        <h1>Accelerating Innovative Ideas into Impactful Research</h1>
        <p>The Sivasakthi Science Foundation (SSF) is committed to nurturing early-stage, high-potential research through our Incubator Research Fund Program. Designed to bridge the critical gap between concept and proof-of-concept, this initiative provides seed funding, strategic guidance, and collaborative opportunities to accelerate promising research ideas in the life sciences, bioinformatics, and AI-driven genomics.</p>
        
        <h2>What We Offer</h2>
        <p><ul><li>Seed Funding: Microgrants and starter funds to test innovative hypotheses or pilot novel research tools.</li><li>Mentorship & Advisory: Access to SSF’s network of experts for strategic guidance on project development, technical execution, and long-term planning.</li><li>Collaborative Platforms: Opportunities to partner with SSF’s research labs, including Bharat Genome Database and GenAi Research Labs.</li><li>Capacity Building: Support in skills development, research design, and proposal preparation to enable future large-scale funding.</li></ul></p>
        
        <br>
        <h2>Who Can Apply</h2>
	<p>The program is open to: <br><ul><li>Early-career researchers and innovators.</li><li>University faculty and research groups exploring new directions.</li><li>Nonprofit and startup teams developing pioneering solutions in genomics, AI, and bioinformatics.</li><li>Student-led initiatives with high potential for societal or scientific impact.</li></ul></p>

	 <br>
        <h2>Areas of Focus</h2>
	<p>We prioritize research aligned with SSF’s mission: <br><ul><li>Genomics & Bioinformatics Innovation</li><li>AI in Life Sciences</li><li>Biodiversity and Conservation Genomics</li><li>Sustainable Biotechnology Solutions</li><li>Healthcare and Precision Medicine Tools</li></ul></p>
		 <br>
        <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
	<p>Transformative research often struggles at the earliest stages due to lack of resources and mentorship. SSF’s Incubator Research Fund is designed to de-risk early ideas, fast-track innovation, and lay the foundation for scalable impact—ensuring that promising concepts don't get left behind.</p>

		 <br>
        <h2>Apply or Collaborate</h2>
	<p>We welcome inquiries from individuals and institutions interested in applying for funding or collaborating on incubator-supported projects. To learn more about eligibility criteria, deadlines, and application guidelines, contact us at info@sivasakthifoundation.org.</p>

